=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09America=01,s economy seems to be cooling. Revised figures for t=
he third quarter=20
showed GDP growing at 2.4% (rather than 2.7%), the slowest for four years.=
=20
The Conference Board=01,s index showed that consumer confidence in November=
 was=20
at its lowest for more than a year. And durable-goods orders fell by 5.5% i=
n=20
October, after rising by 2.4% in the previous month. America=01,s high-tech=
=20
Nasdaq stockmarket had another bad week, falling to just above 2,700, its=
=20
lowest level for more than a year.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Growth slowed in both France and Germany. French GDP growth in =
the third=20
quarter was 2.7 % at an annual rate, compared with 3.3% in the second=20
quarter. Germany=01,s growth slackened off even more strikingly, to 2.3% at=
 an=20
annual rate compared with 4.6% in the previous quarter.=20
